OL,3,CWes Streeting: BMA's plan for resident
OL,4,Cdoctor strike is 'unconscionable'
OL,6,FThe Health Secretary Wes Streeting has
OL,7,Fdescribed the British Medical
OL,8,FAssociation (BMA) as "unconscionable"
OL,9,Fover their advice to resident doctors
OL,10,Fplanning to strike.
OL,12,FThe BMA announced last week that
OL,13,Fresident doctors ` formerly known as
OL,14,Fjunior doctors ` in England would walk
OL,15,Fout for five consecutive days from 7am
OL,16,Fon July 25 amid an ongoing pay dispute
OL,17,Fwith the Government.
