OL,3,CWes Streeting: BMA's plan for resident
OL,4,Cdoctor strike is 'unconscionable'
OL,6,FStreeting's comments come ahead of key
OL,7,Ftalks between the government and the
OL,8,FBMA later this week, aimed at averting
OL,9,Fstrike action.
OL,11,FThe health secretary said earlier on
OL,12,FMonday he was "pleased" the BMA had
OL,13,Faccepted his offer of talks, but
OL,14,Freiterated that the government would
OL,15,Fnot negotiate on pay offers.
OL,17,FInstead, Streeting hopes negotiations
OL,18,Fon other issues facing resident
OL,19,Fdoctors, like career progression will
OL,20,Fbe enough to see of industrial action.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/14
