OL,6,F"We can mitigate against the impact of
OL,7,Fstrikes, and we will, but what we
OL,8,Fcannot do is promise that there will
OL,9,Fbe no consequence and no delay, no
OL,10,Ffurther suffering, because there are
OL,11,Flots of people whose procedures are
OL,12,Fscheduled over that weekend period and
OL,13,Fin the period subsequently, where the
OL,14,FNHS has to recover from the industrial
OL,15,Faction, who will see their operations
OL,16,Fand appointments delayed," Streeting
OL,17,Ftold the committee.
OL,19,F"I have a relative in that position.
